    {
      id: 'types',
      title: 'Types of Jaw Surgery',
      humorLevel: 'low',
      content: `Different procedures for different problems:

**Upper Jaw (Maxillary) Surgery - Le Fort I**
- Moves upper jaw forward, backward, up, or down
- Corrects: Upper jaw underdevelopment, gummy smile, open bite
- Incision: Inside mouth (no visible scar)
- Recovery: 4-6 weeks soft diet

**Lower Jaw (Mandibular) Surgery - BSSO**
(Bilateral Sagittal Split Osteotomy)
- Moves lower jaw forward or backward
- Corrects: Underbite, recessed lower jaw
- Incision: Inside mouth
- Recovery: 4-6 weeks, may require wiring/bands

**Double Jaw Surgery (Bimaxillary)**
- Moves both jaws simultaneously
- Most dramatic changes
- Corrects: Complex deformities, severe cases
- Longer surgery (4-6 hours)
- Most comprehensive result

**Genioplasty (Chin Surgery)**
- Often combined with jaw surgery
- Moves chin bone forward, backward, up, down
- Fine-tunes lower facial profile

**Comparison:**
| Surgery | Duration | Recovery | Impact |
|---------|----------|----------|--------|
| Upper only | 2-3 hrs | 4-6 weeks | Moderate |
| Lower only | 2-3 hrs | 4-6 weeks | Moderate |
| Double jaw | 4-6 hrs | 6-8 weeks | Dramatic |
| With genio | +1-2 hrs | Same | Enhanced |`,
