      id: 'process',
      title: 'The Treatment Process',
      humorLevel: 'low',
      content: `Jaw surgery isn't quick—expect a 2-3 year journey:

**Phase 1: Pre-Surgical Orthodontics (6-18 months)**
- Braces align teeth for surgical positioning
- Teeth may look "worse" temporarily
- Creating space for jaw movement
- Can't be skipped (teeth must fit after move)

**Phase 2: Surgical Planning**
- 3D imaging and computer modeling
- Custom surgical guides created
- Surgical hooks placed on braces
- Pre-op appointments and clearances

**Phase 3: Surgery**
- General anesthesia
- Hospital stay: 1-2 nights usually
- Duration: 2-6 hours depending on type
- Titanium plates and screws placed (permanent)

**Phase 4: Immediate Recovery (1-2 weeks)**
- Significant swelling
- Liquid diet
- May have jaw bands limiting movement
- Pain managed with medication
- Work/school not possible

**Phase 5: Initial Healing (6-8 weeks)**
- Gradual introduction of soft foods
- Swelling decreasing but present
- Limited jaw opening
- Can return to desk work at 2-3 weeks
- No heavy exercise

**Phase 6: Post-Surgical Orthodontics (6-12 months)**
- Fine-tuning bite
- Braces adjusted as healing progresses
- Retainers after braces removed`,
