| Nasal congestion | Especially upper jaw surgery |
| Bite feels "off" initially | Normal, settles with healing |

**Uncommon:**
| Complication | Incidence |
|--------------|-----------|
| Permanent numbness | 5-10% (usually partial) |
| Infection | 1-5% |
| Relapse (movement back) | Variable with retention |
| TMJ issues (new or worsened) | Variable |
| Need for revision | <5% |

**Rare but Serious:**
- Significant blood loss (rare)
- Bad split (bone fractures wrong)
- Hardware issues requiring removal
- Asymmetric results
- Airway compromise

**Nerve Damage:**
The inferior alveolar nerve (feeling in lower lip/chin) runs through the lower jaw. It's stretched during BSSO. Most recover feeling, but some have permanent alteration. This is the most common permanent issue.`,
